 The Ministry of Finance, Budget and National Planning will ensure that the last batch of staff are captured into the Integrated Payroll and Personnel Information System (IPPIS). Mrs Zainab Ahmed made this known while defending the ministry’s 2020 budget estimates before the Senate Committee on Finance on Thursday. Ahmed said that the officers from the Accountant General are already on the field trying to capture the last batch of the staff into the IPPIS. Continue reading Ministry of Finance will capture remaining batch on IPPIS – Minister at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard